This paper addresses challenges in emotion recognition in dialogue systems, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The proposed HiGRU framework utilizes deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of contextual information, which is relevant to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SD). Finally, the paper focuses on emotion recognition in dialogue systems, which is a topic that is relevant to the sub-category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
